<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00375</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING ARTICLES 14, 211, AND 225 OF THE FAMILY CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to amend Articles 14, 211 and 225 of the Family Code to remove the preferential treatment for the father's decision in matters concerning children, from exercising authority over their persons and properties to withholding or giving consent to their child's marriage; harmonize the Family Code with the Magna Carta of Women to serve as responses to our international commitments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BROSAS, ARLENE D., DE JESUS, EMMI A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Zarate (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>2. Elago (007 2016-08-08)</td><tr><td>3. Castro (F.L.) (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>4. Casilao (007 2016-08-08)</td><tr><td>5. Tinio (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>6. Panotes (021 2016-09-13)</td><tr><td>7. Roa-Puno (091 2017-05-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-01-24</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Initial consideration of similar bills (HB Nos. 00219, 00374, 00375,01159, 02386, 03263 and 03951)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Committee Report filed on 2017-02-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-House Committee Report No. 138 substituted by HB No. 5156 (in substitution of HB Nos. 219, 374, 375, 1159, 2386 & 3263</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp3. Scheduled for meet